⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Suburban Dread
node CPS · CPS · ⟦Suburban Dread:CPS:a62354⟧

WHO   — Suburban Dread — the mall and the cul-de-sac
WHAT  — The transposition of Dostoevsky's oppressive St. Petersburg: not heat and crowds but malaise, neglect, and the practiced not-seeing of the comfortable.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel's city is a pressure that breeds the crime; the film's suburb is its update — quieter, colder, just as airless.
HOW   — By beige interiors, watchful adults who don't watch, and a teenage loneliness with nowhere to go.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am Petersburg with a two-car garage — the pressure that makes a numb kid do something unforgivable, then look away from it.

